<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="260" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1870,2041]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="260" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">
We examined eight specimens (
<tableCitation box="[509,593,1870,1897]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,468,494]" captionText="TABLE 1. List of examined and analyzed specimens. Specimens with ID numbers were used for molecular analysis, and L indicates larva." pageId="14" pageNumber="259">Table 1</tableCitation>
), including specimens collected from the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhou &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2008" box="[1250,1388,1870,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palaceus">
<emphasis box="[1250,1388,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">M. palaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1906,1932]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">holotype</typeStatus>
photos of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[372,460,1906,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haui">
<emphasis box="[372,460,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">M. haui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that were provided by Dr. Guanhong Huang from the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department of 
<collectingCountry box="[430,565,1943,1969]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
. Characters of caudal appendages, genitalia and ligula, and body color pattern are coincident among all these individuals. In the molecular phylogeny, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[951,1037,1978,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haui">
<emphasis box="[951,974,1979,2004]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[987,1037,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">haui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhou &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2008" box="[1090,1227,1978,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palaceus">
<emphasis box="[1090,1113,1979,2004]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1127,1227,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">palaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nested in the same clade with strong support (BPP= 0.8) and cannot be further separated (
<figureCitation box="[938,1006,2014,2041]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,496,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-214@20.[211,1375,489,1954]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phylogenetic reconstruction from ITS data modified based on BI and ML trees, with both posterior probabilities (right) and bootstrap values (left) shown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407499/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Most independent evidence supports classifying these two as the same species (
<figureCitation box="[616,683,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1567,1591]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1436,181,1543]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Molecular and morphology-based species delimitation of Megalestes. M: morphological character method; lg: genital ligula; app: caudal appendages, including cerci and paraprocts; GD: genetic distance; TC: traditional classification." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407501/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Therefore, we believe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhou &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2008" box="[950,1086,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palaceus">
<emphasis box="[950,1086,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">M. palaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[1343,1429,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haui">
<emphasis box="[1343,1429,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">M. haui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is known to occur in 
<collectingRegion box="[531,627,187,213]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[682,778,187,213]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[815,882,187,213]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">China</collectingCountry>
and in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1066,1165,187,213]" name="Vietnam" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
